ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.
M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Percent of trials with optimal outcome (i.e., positive over neutral machine) for a nonsocial reward condition
Percent of trials with optimal outcome (i.e., neutral over negative machine) for a nonsocial reward condition
Percent of trials with optimal outcome (i.e., positive over neutral machine) for a social reward condition
Percent of trials with optimal outcome (i.e., neutral over negative machine) for a social reward condition
Percent of trials with optimal outcome (i.e., positive over neutral machine) across nonsocial and social reward conditions
Percent of trials with optimal outcome (i.e., neutral over negative machine) across nonsocial and social reward conditions
Percent of trials with optimal outcome (i.e., positive over neutral or neutral over negative machine) for a nonsocial reward condition
Percent of trials with optimal outcome (i.e., positive over neutral or neutral over negative machine) for a social reward condition
